Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.21,0:00:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were investigating to see if Mizunashi Rena and Hondou Eisuke's sister were the same person...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked to see if Mizunashi Rena's blood type was really AB.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.76,0:00:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have AB blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.09,0:00:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the answer to Eisuke's blood type...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.55,0:00:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was written in the child health record left behind in the mansion where his deceased mother had been a housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.27,0:00:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, it's written right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.52,0:00:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hondou Eisuke, Type O."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.02,0:00:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.86,0:00:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That proves my blood type is O, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.57,0:00:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now all that remains is whether the story about sharing blood with his sister is true or not
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.74,0:00:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that same Okudaira mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.66,0:00:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The son, Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, had been killed by someone one year before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.21,0:00:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is a printout from a video that was recorded at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.42,0:00:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both legs bound, mouth gum taped —\hhow cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.42,0:00:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to know if anyone resented your son or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.85,0:01:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not aware of anyone on the outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.06,0:01:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.23,0:01:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what I believe, Detective Mouri:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.78,0:01:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son Tango's life was cut off by some very crafty person...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.66,0:01:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is living in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.69,0:01:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tingling suspense is building.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running in the darkness —\ha red scream and a black shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.69,0:01:55.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A screams resounds within the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.90,0:01:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.53,0:01:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.20,0:03:34.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,CLASH OF RED AND BLACK\NEXCLAMATION
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.79,0:03:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Your son was killed by someone inside the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it was while everyone in the house was watching a video in the living room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That somebody drowned your son in your pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:56.98,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Okudaira Kakuzou (63)\NHead of Okudaira Family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:04:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember, your son's estimated time of death was between 9:00 and 10:00 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.32,0:04:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For two hours before and after, in other words from 7:00 through 12:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.99,0:04:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you said everyone was watching some videos, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.38,0:04:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much is true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just can't help thinking that Tango's death was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The responsibility of someone in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a secret exit from the living room you can sneak out of or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.77,0:04:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's no secret door, but people did go to the restroom during the course of the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.57,0:04:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.53,0:04:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone snuck outside during a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.53,0:04:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.11,0:04:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The restroom is connected to the living room, and its window isn't large enough for an adult to fit through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.49,0:04:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, wasn't it impossible for anyone in the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.96,0:04:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But look more closely...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:04:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in the picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.67,0:05:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, Tango's right hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.75,0:05:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's wearing a white glove, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.34,0:05:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.13,0:05:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On this exact same day two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.51,0:05:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our previous butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.14,0:05:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fell off a cliff and died while he was driving the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.40,0:05:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the glove he always wore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.36,0:05:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the exact same day?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.24,0:05:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your son was killed on this day just a year ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.79,0:05:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it was today...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.41,0:05:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And three days after my son was killed, the butler's left-hand glove was found here in my study.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.21,0:05:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.46,0:05:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the criminal intended to put both gloves on your son but just happened to miss one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.05,0:05:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone must be holding a grudge over the previous butler's death...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.52,0:05:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A grudge?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.23,0:05:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't the butler's death just an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.44,0:06:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, someone believes you and your son caused that accident
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they put the butler's glove on your son and killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then left the other glove in this room to signal that you were next
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.71,0:06:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were gonna say that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't just come in on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said, "We're done with our other business, so let's go listen to the case."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.35,0:06:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No more "he-he-he."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.02,0:06:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're done, then hurry up and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.24,0:06:50.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been a while, Uncle Kakuzou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.49,0:06:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.28,0:06:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we came across some of your mother's effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.37,0:07:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and thanks to you, I've gotten them safely back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.29,0:07:04.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother was the most wonderful housekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was so compassionate and was always smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for not being as compassionate or friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:17.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tabata Kikuyo (39)\NOkudaira Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, I didn't mean it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.73,0:07:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.15,0:07:24.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:28.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just asking Detective Mouri here to look into it further.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:34.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Segawa Hatarou (48)\NOkudaira Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please show Detective Mouri to the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you wish, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and also, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.83,0:07:40.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make some more coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, while you're at it, call my wife for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.88,0:07:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want her to help me organize the study.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.38,0:07:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as the two of you are available, come and help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.01,0:07:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have something to talk to you about as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.51,0:07:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.18,0:07:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.31,0:07:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.73,0:08:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.98,0:08:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Always knock before you come into my study!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to make that clear to the guests, you dimwit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.37,0:08:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wants me to help him organize the books in his study?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:26.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Okudaira Eiko (56)\NOkudaira's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.62,0:08:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.25,0:08:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man will find fault with every little detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.13,0:08:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earlier, when I tried to open the cardboard box with the set of large books that was delivered today, I really got scolded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.18,0:08:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said, "Don't touch that until I've opened it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's always changing the shelves in his bookcases around to fit those big books...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.56,0:08:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And eventually ends up having to move almost every book.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.94,0:08:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he asks for my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.49,0:08:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll escort Detective Mouri to the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.49,0:09:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That will allow you go to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.91,0:09:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the other things, such as the repairs to Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one has used that car in the last two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can just leave it sit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.38,0:09:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.22,0:09:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the repairs to the car can wait, I'll leave the rest up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.31,0:09:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.89,0:09:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, this is the living room that was mentioned before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.86,0:09:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day all four of us, my husband and myself, the butler and the housekeeper were all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:41.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last year we were watching the videos of our overseas trip on and on for five hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.33,0:09:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't your son watch them with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.91,0:09:48.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it was because he was avoiding being around me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.04,0:09:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I'm not his real mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.84,0:09:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.88,0:09:55.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.22,0:09:57.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was my husband's son with his former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.93,0:09:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.89,0:10:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, are you sure my husband didn't say anything about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.85,0:10:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him suspecting us just because they haven't caught any culprits, my husband is becoming annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The attached restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An adult definitely couldn't get through this window.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no way to just secretly slip out of the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.04,0:10:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since all four of them were watching those videos here, they have perfect alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.96,0:10:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.05,0:10:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.13,0:10:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw that Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, who was such a crybaby,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,brought such a cute girlfriend along with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.64,0:10:42.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-She isn't my girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We came because we wanted to know Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}'s blood type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.36,0:10:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said you'd found his child health records.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.82,0:11:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.66,0:11:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's this about your blood type?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.20,0:11:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I showed a picture of my sister to Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he said, "Isn't she that announcer, Mizunashi Rena?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.38,0:11:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we came here to clear up any uncertainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.04,0:11:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, that announcer has Type AB, while I have O.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.47,0:11:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since I received a transfusion from my sister, my sister and that announcer must be different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.93,0:11:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} already knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, I remember that happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.60,0:11:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was right after his mother died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.98,0:11:39.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was taken in by his father and moved to Osaka, that accident happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as I heard about it, I dashed right over there and found his sister sleeping beside his bed, completely exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:12:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked the nurse why, she said his sister had given him a large amount of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.22,0:12:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she told them, "You can draw out all of my blood for my little brother."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that what she said?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.81,0:12:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That settles it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.65,0:12:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister and Mizunashi Rena...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are not the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really watch that much TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.54,0:12:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they really that much alike?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.54,0:12:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister and that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.08,0:12:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:35.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the photo we saw, they were two halves of a melon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.75,0:12:37.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless they're doppelgangers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having two people who look so completely alike...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.88,0:12:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's connected to my sister's disappearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.51,0:12:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.68,0:12:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.31,0:12:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He became suspicious of Mizunashi Rena.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.77,0:12:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then checked Uncle out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.81,0:12:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to obtain an invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:12:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he intended to ask her about his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.78,0:13:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He likely expects she would feign ignorance if he approached her directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why not meet her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, her...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.99,0:13:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might as well have them show us the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.79,0:13:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might discover something there about the son's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.54,0:13:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.33,0:13:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.01,0:13:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.13,0:13:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you go out somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we were out of milk for the coffee, so we out to buy some in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.68,0:13:33.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, forgive me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you show everyone to the pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.40,0:13:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take in the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.19,0:13:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.19,0:13:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, this place is dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been left this way since the incident a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.13,0:14:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.38,0:14:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the pool I always used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.97,0:14:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, this kid's clumsy no matter where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.35,0:14:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's the right size.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.11,0:14:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope my deceased son's clothes are of a size that fits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.49,0:14:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.41,0:14:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It fits well, so I guess he was also short?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.87,0:14:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is a little baggy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.91,0:14:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.54,0:14:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tango{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was known as a body builder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your clothes are in the washer now, so wait for a bit, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I didn't see any coffee in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left it ready in the coffee maker before I went to go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.26,0:14:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.81,0:14:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see the coffee in the kitchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.85,0:15:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Master might have grown impatient and made it himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.53,0:15:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounded like it came from the Master's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.03,0:15:09.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.82,0:15:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hope it wasn't that expensive vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.49,0:15:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.20,0:15:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's always treasured that vase, considering it's worth ¥50,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A blackout...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.63,0:15:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.92,0:15:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.36,0:15:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:52.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go in, Mistress! On the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.87,0:15:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.62,0:15:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.13,0:16:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.79,0:16:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's hurry and get him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, call for an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.34,0:16:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, what's with this rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not coming undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.49,0:16:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the rim of the vase...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid it was too late by the time he made it to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.59,0:16:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.06,0:16:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.43,0:17:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.19,0:17:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.36,0:17:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's all right, I have two or three questions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.20,0:17:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who first discovered the body was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.91,0:17:21.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first ones to discover my husband were Kikuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Segawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard the sound of something breaking coming from the study, so we rushed here and knocked on the door, but he didn't respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.38,0:17:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he didn't answer when we called out, but when we started turning the door knob, he shouted, "Don't open it."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.60,0:17:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, did you open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.35,0:17:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.89,0:17:51.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we opened the door, we found the master's body hanging there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.07,0:17:55.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he did it just before you opened the door, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, his body was still swaying then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.45,0:18:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure we're talking suicide here, since the windows were securely locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he say, "Don't open it"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's obviously because he didn't want anyone to see him dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.30,0:18:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason he had grown tired of, the world and chose death instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.64,0:18:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.89,0:18:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at the fragments of the vase scattered on the floor, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.68,0:18:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must have been the source of the breaking sound we heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, this is a vase he cherished more than anything else and it's worth ¥50,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.15,0:18:35.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,¥50,000,000!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.36,0:18:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.70,0:18:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.91,0:18:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always talked about it, saying even ¥200,000,000 couldn't make up for that vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.87,0:18:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even used that vase as a footstool in order to kill himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.58,0:18:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Further proving he'd grown to hate this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.37,0:18:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The autopsy results say they found coffee and sleeping pills in the corpse's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.38,0:18:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:18:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are there two cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them was mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would he bother to take sleeping pills with the coffee before hanging himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.60,0:19:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he originally planned to take a lot of sleeping pills, but he got impatient and decided to change the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this time he applied glue to the knot of the rope to be sure it wouldn't come undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.45,0:19:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glue?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.70,0:19:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.66,0:19:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we were getting him down, we had a hard time getting the rope undone due to it being glued.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.67,0:19:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what reason did he have to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.84,0:19:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do any of you have any idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.13,0:19:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.59,0:19:44.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He requested we come to the study so he could tell us something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.05,0:19:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe he was distressed about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.18,0:19:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, why did he hang himself before discussing it with you all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have thought discussing it with us wouldn't help...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.52,0:19:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.53,0:20:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your husband didn't trust you very much, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.16,0:20:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood running from his mouth is likely from him biting his lip in regret
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.16,0:20:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't stand someone else inheriting his prize vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.29,0:20:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That must be why he broke it by using it as a footstool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.67,0:20:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means he was really greedy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.97,0:20:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.89,0:20:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if he had used the vase as a footstool and it only made the noise when it fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.64,0:20:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have already hung himself, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he weren't so greedy, he wouldn't have shouted "Don't take the vase" after that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.78,0:20:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't "Don't take" it was "Don't open."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.32,0:20:47.08,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: {\i1}Ageru na{\i0} means "Don't take", while {\i1}Akeru na{\i0} means "Don't open"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.41,0:20:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, that is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could someone hanging really be able to shout?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.87,0:20:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This means that when the vase broke, he hadn't hung himself yet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.04,0:20:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he was so shocked after breaking the vase that he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.01,0:21:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if you rushed here immediately after hearing it break, he didn't have time to prepare the rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.05,0:21:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was because of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.76,0:21:14.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Killer from {\b1}Hades{\b0}\NShinmei Kaori
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.10,0:21:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, this book is stained with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.97,0:21:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have been upset if it were one of his important books.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.77,0:21:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Killer from Hades"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does seem to have been directly below his feet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:28.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.33,0:21:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.21,0:21:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were, the murderer must be a ghost from the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.17,0:21:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.71,0:21:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.42,0:21:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The word "Hades" is mostly covered in blood, and the droplets below resemble the "ko" character in hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.85,0:21:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Yomi-ko"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.10,0:21:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,(Calendar)\N"Ko-yomi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.10,0:21:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it something about a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.10,0:21:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure whether this is "ko" or not
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.52,0:22:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do this and turn it horizontally, it resembles the hiragana "i" as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.65,0:22:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if this really was a dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the master of the house, Kakuzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.74,0:22:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murdered by someone inside of this very house.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.52,0:24:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does the message left in blood mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.11,0:24:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cruel method.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.86,0:24:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The full extent of which we yet to grasp.
